My basic .vim setup

INSTALLATION
============
assuming dotvim's cloned in a user's home directory.....

--
git clone git://github.com/gberenfield/dotvim.git
ln -s ~/dotvim ~/.vim
ln -s ~/dotvim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s ~/dotvim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
mkdir -p ~/dotvim/backup

git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle
vim -u ~/.vim/bundles.vim +BundleInstall +q
--

Taglist requires exuberant-ctags to be installed on the system
http://ctags.sourceforge.net


VIMCLOJURE NOTES
----------------
http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=2501

in ~/.vim/bundle/VimClojure you'll need to manually install the client/ directory from the source repository
https://bitbucket.org/kotarak/vimclojure

The server can be downloaded at
http://clojars.org/repo/vimclojure/server/

The server setting below is machine dependent and should be stored in ~/.vimrc.local
let vimclojure#NailgunClient = "/Users/mc/.vim/bundle/vimclojure/client/ng"

OPENING FILES NICELY
--------------------
Removed command-t. Not for me.
Use peepopen (if on mac) or molly instead

VIMPAGER
--------
git://github.com/rkitover/vimpager.git

